    <h2 id="why-lions-mane">Why Lion's Mane Is the Most Promising Nootropic Mushroom</h2>

    <p>Lion's mane (<em>Hericium erinaceus</em>) has been used in traditional Chinese and Japanese medicine for centuries, but modern neuroscience is revealing why. This mushroom produces two unique classes of compounds — hericenones and erinacines — that cross the blood-brain barrier and directly stimulate Nerve Growth Factor (NGF) synthesis. NGF is a protein critical for neuron survival, growth, and repair. No other natural food or supplement has been shown to stimulate NGF production with this specificity.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
