      <p>A landmark 2009 double-blind, placebo-controlled trial published in <em>Phytotherapy Research</em> found that adults aged 50-80 who consumed <strong>3g of lion's mane daily for 16 weeks</strong> showed significantly improved cognitive function scores compared to placebo. Scores declined after supplementation was discontinued, suggesting ongoing use is necessary to maintain benefits.</p>
